[{"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Pattern recognition in high-dimensional spaces\n\u2212Problems arise when performing recognition in a high-dimensional \nspace (curse of dimensionality).\n\u2212Significant improvements can be achieved by first mapping the data \ninto a lower-dimensional sub-space.\n\u2212The goal of PCA is to reduce the dimensionality of the data while \nretaining as much as possible of the variation present in the original \ndataset.\n2", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 0}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Dimensionality reduction\n\u2212PCA allows us to compute a linear transformation that maps data \nfrom a high dimensional space to a lower dimensional sub-space.\n3", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 1}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Lower dimensionality basis\n\u2212Approximate vectors by finding a basis in an appropriate lower \ndimensional space.\n(1) Higher-dimensional space representation:\n(2) Lower-dimensional space representation:\n4", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 2}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Example\n5", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 3}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Information loss\n\u2212Dimensionality reduction implies information loss !!\n\u2212Want to preserve as much information as possible, that is:\n\u2022 How to determine the best lower dimensional sub-space?\n6", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 4}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Methodology\n\u2212Suppose x1, x2, ..., xM are N x 1 vectors\n7", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 5}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Methodology \u2013 cont.\n8", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 6}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Linear transformation implied by PCA\n\u2212The linear transformation RN \u2192RK that performs the dimensionality \nreduction is:\n9", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 7}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Geometric interpretation\n\u2212PCA projects the data along the directions where the data varies the \nmost.\n\u2212These directions are determined by the eigenvectors of the \ncovariance matrix corresponding to the largest eigenvalues.\n\u2212The magnitude of the eigenvalues corresponds to the variance of \nthe data along the eigenvector directions.\n10", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 8}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 How to choose the principal components?\n\u2212To choose K, use the following criterion:\n11", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 9}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 What is the error due to dimensionality reduction?\n\u2212We saw above that an original vector x can be reconstructed using \nits principal components:\n\u2212It can be shown that the low-dimensional basis based on principal \ncomponents minimizes the reconstruction error:\n\u2212It can be shown that the error is equal to:\n12", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 10}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Standardization\n\u2212The principal components are dependent on the units used to \nmeasure the original variables as well as on the range of values \nthey assume.\n\u2212We should always standardize the data prior to using PCA.\n\u2212A common standardization method is to transform all the data to \nhave zero mean and unit standard deviation:\n13", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 11}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 PCA and classification\n\u2212PCA is not always an optimal dimensionality-reduction procedure \nfor classification purposes:\n14", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 12}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Case Study: Eigenfaces for Face Detection/Recognition\n\u2212M. Turk, A. Pentland, \"Eigenfaces for Recognition\", Journal of \nCognitive Neuroscience, vol. 3, no. 1, pp. 71-86, 1991.\n\u2022 Face Recognition\n\u2212The simplest approach is \nto think of it as a template \nmatching problem\n\u2212Problems arise when performing \nrecognition in a high-dimensional \nspace.\n\u2212Significant improvements can be \nachieved by first mapping the data \ninto a lower dimensionality space.", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 13}}, {"page_content": "into a lower dimensionality space.\n\u2212How to find this lower-dimensional \nspace?\n15", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 13}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Main idea behind eigenfaces\n16", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 14}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Computation of the eigenfaces\n17", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 15}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Computation of the eigenfaces \u2013 cont.\n18", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 16}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Computation of the eigenfaces \u2013 cont.\n19", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 17}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Computation of the eigenfaces \u2013 cont.\n20", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 18}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Representing faces onto this basis\n21", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 19}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Representing faces onto this basis \u2013 cont.\n22", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 20}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Face Recognition Using Eigenfaces\n23", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 21}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Face Recognition Using Eigenfaces \u2013 cont.\n\u2212The distance er is called distance within the face space (difs)\n\u2212Comment: we can use the common Euclidean distance to compute \ner, however, it has been reported that the Mahalanobis distance \nperforms better:\n24", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 22}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Face Detection Using Eigenfaces\n25", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 23}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Face Detection Using Eigenfaces \u2013 cont.\n26", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 24}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Reconstruction of \nfaces and non-faces\n27", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 25}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Time requirements\n\u2212About 400 ms (Lisp, Sun4, 128x128 images)\n\u2022 Applications\n\u2212Face detection, tracking, and recognition\n28", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 26}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Problems\n\u2212Background (de-emphasize the outside of the face \u2013 e.g., by \nmultiplying the input image by a 2D Gaussian window centered on \nthe face)\n\u2212Lighting conditions (performance degrades with light changes)\n\u2212Scale (performance decreases quickly with changes to head size)\n\u2212multi-scale eigenspaces\n\u2212scale input image to multiple sizes\n\u2212Orientation (performance decreases but not as fast as with scale \nchanges)\n\u2212plane rotations can be handled", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 27}}, {"page_content": "changes)\n\u2212plane rotations can be handled\n\u2212out-of-plane rotations are more difficult to handle\n29", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 27}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Experiments\n\u221216 subjects, 3 orientations, 3 sizes\n\u22123 lighting conditions, 6 resolutions (512x512 ... 16x16)\n\u2212Total number of images: 2,592\n30", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 28}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Experiment 1\n\u2212Used various sets of 16 images for training\n\u2212One image/person, taken under the same conditions\n\u2212Eigenfaces were computed offline (7 eigenfaces used)\n\u2212Classify the rest images as one of the 16 individuals\n\u2212No rejections (no threshold for difs)\n\u2212Performed a large number of experiments and averaged the results:\n\u221296% correct averaged over light variation\n\u221285% correct averaged over orientation variation\n\u221264% correct averaged over size variation\n31", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 29}}, {"page_content": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n\u2022 Experiment 2\n\u2212They considered rejections (by thresholding difs)\n\u2212There is a tradeoff between correct recognition and rejections.\n\u2212Adjusting the threshold to achieve 100% recognition accuracy \nresulted in:\n\u221219% rejections while varying lighting\n\u221239% rejections while varying orientation\n\u221260% rejections while varying size\n\u2022 Experiment 3\n\u2212Reconstruction using \npartial information\n32", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 30}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Multiple classes and PCA\n\u2212Suppose there are C classes in the training data.\n\u2212PCA is based on the sample covariance which characterizes the \nscatter of the entire data set, irrespective of class-membership.\n\u2212The projection axes chosen by PCA might not provide good \ndiscrimination power.\n\u2022 What is the goal of LDA?\n\u2212Perform dimensionality reduction while preserving as much of the \nclass discriminatory information as possible.", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 31}}, {"page_content": "class discriminatory information as possible.\n\u2212Seeks to find directions along which the classes are best separated.\n\u2212Takes into consideration the scatter within-classes but also the \nscatter between-classes.\n\u2212More capable of distinguishing image variation due to identity from \nvariation due to other sources such as illumination and expression.\n33", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 31}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Methodology\n34", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 32}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Methodology \u2013 cont.\n\u2212LDA computes a transformation that maximizes the between-class \nscatter while minimizing the within-class scatter:\n\u2212Such a transformation should retain class separability while \nreducing the variation due to sources other than identity (e.g., \nillumination).\n35", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 33}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Linear transformation implied by LDA\n\u2212The linear transformation is given by a matrix U whose columns are \nthe eigenvectors of Sw\n-1 Sb (called Fisherfaces).\n\u2212The eigenvectors are solutions of the generalized eigenvector\nproblem:\n36", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 34}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Does Sw\n-1 always exist?\n\u2212If Sw is non-singular, we can obtain a conventional eigenvalue \nproblem by writing:\n\u2212In practice, Sw is often singular since the data are image vectors \nwith large dimensionality while the size of the data set is much \nsmaller (M << N )\n37", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 35}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Does Sw\n-1 always exist? \u2013 cont.\n\u2212To alleviate this problem, we can perform two projections:\n1) PCA is first applied to the data set to reduce its dimensionality.\n2) LDA is then applied to further reduce the dimensionality.\n38", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 36}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Case Study: Using Discriminant Eigenfeatures for Image \nRetrieval\n\u2212D. Swets, J. Weng, \"Using Discriminant Eigenfeatures for Image \nRetrieval\", IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine \nIntelligence, vol. 18, no. 8, pp. 831-836, 1996.\n\u2022 Content-based image retrieval\n\u2212The application being studied here is query-by-example image \nretrieval.\n\u2212The paper deals with the problem of selecting a good set of image \nfeatures for content-based image retrieval.\n39", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 37}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Assumptions\n\u2212\"Well-framed\" images are required as input for training and query-\nby-example test probes.\n\u2212Only a small variation in the size, position, and orientation of the \nobjects in the images is allowed.\n40", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 38}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Some terminology\n\u2212Most Expressive Features (MEF): the features (projections) \nobtained using PCA.\n\u2212Most Discriminating Features (MDF): the features (projections) \nobtained using LDA.\n\u2022 Computational considerations\n\u2212When computing the eigenvalues/eigenvectors of Sw\n-1SBuk = \u03bbkuk\nnumerically, the computations can be unstable since Sw\n-1SB is not \nalways symmetric.\n\u2212See paper for a way to find the eigenvalues/eigenvectors in a stable \nway.", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 39}}, {"page_content": "way.\n\u2212Important: Dimensionality of LDA is bounded by C-1 --- this is the \nrank of Sw\n-1SB\n41", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 39}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Factors unrelated to classification\n\u2212MEF vectors show the tendency of PCA to capture major variations \nin the training set such as lighting direction.\n\u2212MDF vectors discount those factors unrelated to classification.\n42", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 40}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Clustering effect\n1)\nGenerate the set of MEFs for each image in the training set.\n2)\nGiven an query image, compute its MEFs using the same \nprocedure.\n3)\nFind the k closest neighbors for retrieval (e.g., using Euclidean \ndistance).\n\u2022 Methodology\n43", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 41}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Experiments and results\n\u2212Face images\n\u2212A set of face images was used with 2 expressions, 3 lighting conditions.\n\u2212Testing was performed using a disjoint set of images - one image, \nrandomly chosen, from each individual.\n44", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 42}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n45", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 43}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2212correct search probes\n46", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 44}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2212failed search probe\n47", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 45}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Case Study: PCA versus LDA\n\u2212A. Martinez, A. Kak, \"PCA versus LDA\", IEEE Transactions on \nPattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence, vol. 23, no. 2, pp. 228-\n233, 2001.\n\u2022 Is LDA always better than PCA?\n\u2212There has been a tendency in the computer vision community to \nprefer LDA over PCA.\n\u2212This is mainly because LDA deals directly with discrimination \nbetween classes while PCA does not pay attention to the underlying \nclass structure.", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 46}}, {"page_content": "class structure.\n\u2212This paper shows that when the training set is small, PCA can \noutperform LDA.\n\u2212When the number of samples is large and representative for each \nclass, LDA outperforms PCA.\n48", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 46}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Is LDA always better than PCA? \u2013 cont.\n49", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 47}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Is LDA always better than PCA? \u2013 cont.\n50", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 48}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Is LDA always better than PCA? \u2013 cont.\n51", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 49}}, {"page_content": "Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA)\n\u2022 Critique of LDA\n\u2212Only linearly separable classes will remain separable after applying \nLDA.\n\u2212It does not seem to be superior to PCA when the training data set is \nsmall.\n52", "metadata": {"producer": "iLovePDF", "creator": "", "creationdate": "", "source": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "file_path": "./temp_uploads\\95898357-0dad-403b-9527-a1fc60a1e152_FR_PCA_LDA- Theory.pdf", "total_pages": 51, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2026-02-18T10:06:42+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20260218100642Z", "creationDate": "", "page": 50}}]